				\begin{document}$${N}_{{\mathrm{{cPC}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M12"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>N</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">cPC</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq5.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the number of contrasted principal components with <inline-formula id="IEq6"><alternatives><tex-math id="M13">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\lambda }_{j}^{{\mathrm{{norm}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M14"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>λ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">norm</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq6.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> over a predefined cut-off value (i.e. 0.025), <inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M15">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\omega }_{i,j}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M16"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ω</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq7.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the loading/weight of the feature <italic>i</italic> on the component <italic>j</italic>, and <inline-formula id="IEq8"><alternatives><tex-math id="M17">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${N}_{{\mathrm{{features}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M18"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>N</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">features</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq8.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the total number of features considered in the dimensionality reduction analysis.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec19">
      <title>ESM definition</title>
      <p id="Par49">The brain is modeled as a system with <italic>N</italic><sub>rois</sub> structurally interconnected gray matter regions<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR12">12</xref></sup> covering the brain’s whole gray matter (in this study, <italic>N</italic><sub>rois</sub> = 78 based on a known anatomical brain parcellation<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR48">48</xref></sup>), where each region <italic>i</italic> (<inline-formula id="IEq9"><alternatives><tex-math id="M19">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$i=1..{N}_{{\mathrm{{rois}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M20"><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>.</mml:mo><mml:mo>.</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>N</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">rois</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq9.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>) is characterized by its temporal value (<italic>S</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub>) of infection-like “agent” (inf-A) accumulation (e.g. misfolded protein [MP] burden). Notice that <italic>S</italic> can also be defined in probabilistic terms (see <italic>NeuroPM-box</italic> tutorial). The dynamic of this system, in terms of inf-A propagation and accumulation, will depend on the interactions between the inf-A “infected” and “non-infected” regions, with temporal changes in the regional <italic>S</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub> values described by the non-linear differential equation:<disp-formula id="Equ2"><label>2</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M21">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{{\mathrm{d}}{S}_{i}}{{{\mathrm{d}}t}}=\left(1-{S}_{i}\left(t\right)/{\max }S\right){\varepsilon }_{i}\left(t\right)-{\delta }_{i}\left(t\right){S}_{i}\left(t\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M22"><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">d</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">d</mml:mi><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>/</mml:mo><mml:mi>max</mml:mi><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ε</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_Equ2.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
      <p id="Par50">The first term on the right side of Eq. (<xref rid="Equ2" ref-type="">2</xref>) represents the regional likelihood (or probability) of receiving infectious-like “agents” (<inline-formula id="IEq10"><alternatives><tex-math id="M23">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\varepsilon }_{i}\left(t\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M24"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ε</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq10.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>) if region <italic>i</italic> is “non-infected”, where <inline-formula id="IEq11"><alternatives><tex-math id="M25">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\max }S$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M26"><mml:mi>max</mml:mi><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq11.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the maximum possible <italic>S</italic> value (defined across all the population). The second term corresponds to the likelihood (or probability) of being clean of inf-A at time <italic>t</italic> (<inline-formula id="IEq12"><alternatives><tex-math id="M27">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\delta }_{i}\left(t\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M28"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq12.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>) if region <italic>i</italic> was “infected” before. To consider the fact that a particular “infected” sub-region in brain region <italic>i</italic> can potentially “infect” neighboring sub-regions, <inline-formula id="IEq13"><alternatives><tex-math id="M29">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\rm{\varepsilon }}}_{{\rm{i}}}\left({{t}}\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M30"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">ε</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq13.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is modeled as the accumulation of exogenous and endogenous infectious-like factors:<disp-formula id="Equ3"><label>3</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M31">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\varepsilon }_{i}\left(t\right)=\mathop{\sum}\limits_{j\ne i}{{Pa}}_{j\to i}{\beta }_{j}^{{\mathrm{{ext}}}}\left(t\right){S}_{j}\left(t\right)+{{{Pa}}_{i\to i}{\beta }_{i}^{{\mathrm{{int}}}}\left(t\right)S}_{i}\left(t\right),$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M32"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ε</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:munder><mml:mrow><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo>≠</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:munder><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">ext</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">int</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_Equ3.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where <inline-formula id="IEq14"><alternatives><tex-math id="M33">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{Pa}}_{j\to i}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M34"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq14.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the weighted anatomical connection value between the regions <italic>j</italic> and <italic>i</italic>, <inline-formula id="IEq15"><alternatives><tex-math id="M35">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{j}^{{\mathrm{{ext}}}}\left(t\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M36"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">ext</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq15.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the extrinsic “infection” rate of region <italic>j</italic>, and <inline-formula id="IEq16"><alternatives><tex-math id="M37">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{i}^{{\mathrm{{int}}}}\left(t\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M38"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">int</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq16.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the intrinsic “infection” rate. We assume that inf-A diffuse from regions of higher concentration to regions of lower concentration. With a high inequality in the inf-A accumulation levels of all the regions causing an increase in the extrinsic propagation across the entire brain, and a decrease in the intrinsic fraction that stays in each seed region. These effects are modeled as<disp-formula id="Equ4"><label>4</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M39">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{i}^{{\mathrm{{ext}}}}(t)=g{(t)\beta }_{i}(t),$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M40"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">ext</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_Equ4.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula><disp-formula id="Equa"><alternatives><tex-math id="M41">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{i}^{{\mathrm{{int}}}}(t)=(1-g(t)){\beta }_{i}(t),$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M42"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">int</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_Equa.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where <italic>g(t)</italic> is a global tuning variable (<italic>Gini</italic> coefficient<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR54">54</xref></sup>) that quantifies the temporal inf-A accumulation inequality among the different brain regions, and <inline-formula id="IEq17"><alternatives><tex-math id="M43">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{i}={\beta }_{i}^{{\mathrm{{ext}}}}+{\beta }_{i}^{{\mathrm{{int}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M44"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">ext</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">int</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq17.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the total “infection” rate of the region <italic>i</italic>. A value of 0 for <italic>g</italic> reflects perfect equality across all regions, and a value of 1 corresponds to a complete inequality.</p>
      <p id="Par51">In the <italic>NeuroPM-box</italic>, clearance and production rates can be modeled as constant values (<inline-formula id="IEq18"><alternatives><tex-math id="M45">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{o}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M46"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>o</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq18.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, <inline-formula id="IEq19"><alternatives><tex-math id="M47">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\delta }_{o}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M48"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>o</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq19.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>) across all regions or as sigmoid functions depending on the local <italic>S</italic> values. When opting for a sigmoid relationship, <inline-formula id="IEq20"><alternatives><tex-math id="M49">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
