				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${S}_{i}\left(t\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M60"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq24.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and a constant parameter. However, the regional capacity to clear/remove infectious-like agents will decrease with the increase in inf-A accumulation, following a decreasing exponential relationship:<disp-formula id="Equ6"><label>6</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M61">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
