				\begin{document}$${S}_{i}^{m} &gt; 0$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M90"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>&gt;</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq37.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> for non-alteration, decrease, or increment, respectively). In general, this system is defined by the [<italic>N</italic><sub>factors</sub><italic>N</italic><sub>rois</sub> × 1] state space vector <inline-formula id="IEq38"><alternatives><tex-math id="M91">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
