				\begin{document}$$A(t)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M94"><mml:mi>A</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq39.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, the <italic>dynamic multifactorial direct interaction network</italic>, where each directed edge corresponds to a factor–factor or a region–region interaction.</p>
      <p id="Par54">The dynamic behavior of the proposed brain system will depend on (i) the local direct interactions among all the biological factors, constrained within each brain region, (ii) the potential propagation of factor-specific alterations through “physical” networks (i.e. anatomical and/or vascular networks), and (iii) the influence of external inputs. These processes can be described by the differential equation model:<disp-formula id="Equ8"><label>8</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M95">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\left\{\begin{array}{c}\frac{{\mathrm{d}}{\boldsymbol{S}}}{{{\mathrm{d}}t}}=A\left(t\right)S{\boldsymbol{+}}{Bu},\\ {\mathrm{{Cog}}}=\beta S,\end{array}\right.$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M96"><mml:mfenced open="{"><mml:mrow><mml:mtable><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="center"><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">d</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="bold-italic">S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">d</mml:mi><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>A</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="bold-italic">+</mml:mi><mml:mi>B</mml:mi><mml:mi>u</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:mtd></mml:mtr><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="center"><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">Cog</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_Equ8.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where <inline-formula id="IEq40"><alternatives><tex-math id="M97">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$A(t)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M98"><mml:mi>A</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="42003_2021_2133_Article_IEq40.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is a [<italic>N</italic><sub>factors</sub><italic>N</italic><sub>rois</sub> × <italic>N</italic><sub>factors</sub><italic>N</italic><sub>rois</sub>] asymmetric network/matrix characterizing all the multifactorial interactions at time <italic>t</italic>. It depends on model parameters that are estimated during model fitting, and on the brain’s connection properties, estimated a priori. <inline-formula id="IEq41"><alternatives><tex-math id="M99">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
